<subSubSection id="2172EDECB539AFE4DD00A063297826C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0F007E7879E59CB807D6BD2782BED6EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E6701D0B44D1DC22FF058AB31A56842" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
The specific epithet is a noun in apposition and refers to a specific 
<taxonomicName id="1E3973BD765CDF1BAF4ACEA4D83CC709" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Salsa</taxonomicName>
dancing style, Rueda de Casino, in which changing pairs of dancers from a circle and dance moves are being called out by a single person. It is a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
<caption id="F80BF3C6F0E8792FECB6A65A685CAE04" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" start="Figure 19" startId="F19">
<paragraph id="D76B905DC437D8797F2BDB3BAB81EEB5" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="42FF9571013238BF25C0301F3E5FE43C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Figure 19.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="3A5C180384B9AD33E880F2E836D4F291" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa rueda" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rueda">
<emphasis id="C168312ECDE27608F972C549FB92B474" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa rueda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., male holotype (MV K-14856) 
<emphasis id="849C8A36EAFDAAE4B71E26915AB19776" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A</emphasis>
dorsal habitus 
<emphasis id="4FEFC49238A1EB2E2372B4B1EA92927E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">B</emphasis>
ventral habitus 
<emphasis id="4C3C0C69FB53E851E0AC20FA41B46439" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C</emphasis>
left pedipalp, ventral view 
<emphasis id="D2BC4EFA9B05BCB15F1D1F1AF1E4B989" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">D</emphasis>
left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (
<emphasis id="75DC80A6DB039B06B1023C6D9F6F29AF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A, B</emphasis>
); 0.2 mm (
<emphasis id="7A2702253651078F4024A0384A642858" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C, D</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="36F26DA4B83FC01746D39041F61AFACB" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1A483AB6FA34480DC543E5D39EB177A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40BAD45D46FAB426F5BB4F79F76E22B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="41A5B4B22115E9465EB64BF15B229AD4" genus="S." lsidName="S. rueda" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="rueda">
<emphasis id="2F273084E31C7F5D731FB410202908FE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. rueda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. are identified from all other species of the genus by the highly elongated median apophysis of the pedipalp and the enlarged basal, curved prong on the terminal apophysis (Figs 
<figureCitation id="686F1ACE9614E383FE246E8F81610E73" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Salsa rueda sp. nov., expanded left pedipalp of male holotype (MV K- 14856) A ventral view B baso-ventral view C apico-ventral view D apical view. Arrow in A, B points to the tubercle on median apophysis arch. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686602" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">3A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="0BD0918E6CF9A69C03F1889FE7A4BA13" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19C</figureCitation>
). Females can be distinguished from all other species by shape of the epigyne base, which is much longer than wide and has a central longitudinal ridge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C379936FAC960F938C7AB881B946556E" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="01F14933247D99352BFC75FBB0A8FFA7" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="description">
<paragraph id="37153031A7D00DCC8E109FA1D196DB00" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="225E1B90EA94EE6849F42093CBA33341" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="FB972B33B62D94D861F6BB0203FD56BC" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Male</emphasis>
(based on holotype, MV K-14856). Total length 6.1. Carapace 3.3 long, 2.6 wide, brown, slightly paler in cephalic area and posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="91BC5683BC5BE6CF8F6B06C478959E9D" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.16, ALE 0.14, PME 0.09, PLE 0.09; row of eyes: AME 0.47, PME 0.43, PLE 1.37. Chelicerae orange-brown; with four promarginal teeth (basal and apical largest) and three retromarginal teeth (basal largest). Legs shades of brown, femora basally yellow-brown in legs II, III and IV (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FCFBFD992F3CFEEE8DAD8B9841C9555A" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19A, B</figureCitation>
). Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 4.5 + 1.5 + 2.8 + 2.6 + 1.0 = 12.4, II - 3.0 + 1.4 + 2.0 + 2.4 + 0.9 = 9.7, III - 1.7 + 0.9 + 1.2 + 1.2 + 0.6 = 5.6, IV - 2.6 + 1.1 + 1.8 + 2.2 + 0.8 = 8.5. Labium 0.36 long, 0.56, brown; endites brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="661D0F68CC1A46C4901C7ED732FB646D" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.5 long, 1.2 wide, dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B2B5B7E736141AFDF02514BEFDBCF4B8" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 2.7 long, 2.6 wide, dorsal folium uniformly olive-grey bordered by broad wavy pale bands (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9AF9355F54E33940E9B08588467B7730" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19A</figureCitation>
); venter dark olive-grey with two ovoid lateral white patches (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CB116862EB5DE584ED90DEFE4CD6DDBD" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + cymbium = total length): 0.6 + 0.2 + 0.1 + 1.1 = 2.0; paracymbium slightly curved with conspicuous base (Figs 
<figureCitation id="373CEE08C056EADEAAD47B4C25062663" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Salsa rueda sp. nov., expanded left pedipalp of male holotype (MV K- 14856) A ventral view B baso-ventral view C apico-ventral view D apical view. Arrow in A, B points to the tubercle on median apophysis arch. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686602" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">3A, B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B72D187384195A0271037E1D0308BD20" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19D</figureCitation>
); median apophysis bearing a rounded basal process, elongated C-shaped; basal arch with numerous tubercles (Figs 
<figureCitation id="5266E5C913A02E05F6B10968C368A31C" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Salsa rueda sp. nov., expanded left pedipalp of male holotype (MV K- 14856) A ventral view B baso-ventral view C apico-ventral view D apical view. Arrow in A, B points to the tubercle on median apophysis arch. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686602" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">3A-D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="64852A0DDA1DCE15E0F3F36BB0E5BC12" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19C</figureCitation>
); conductor lobe broad (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E5C37C99D8B0B934A1A6A7BA814E1D0A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Salsa rueda sp. nov., expanded left pedipalp of male holotype (MV K- 14856) A ventral view B baso-ventral view C apico-ventral view D apical view. Arrow in A, B points to the tubercle on median apophysis arch. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686602" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">3A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B1151E1B4B388734637F8559A743B9D1" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19C</figureCitation>
); terminal apophysis sub-rectangular with a curved, heavily sclerotised basal prong (Figs 
<figureCitation id="96B6F84FF89DD071C4647C5661C758CF" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Salsa rueda sp. nov., expanded left pedipalp of male holotype (MV K- 14856) A ventral view B baso-ventral view C apico-ventral view D apical view. Arrow in A, B points to the tubercle on median apophysis arch. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686602" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">3A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="67080CEEFC187C150F8FE55265CF4714" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19C</figureCitation>
); conductor heavily sclerotised, spatulate (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E71025703C3E6ADD82598DE1992FE0CA" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Salsa rueda sp. nov., expanded left pedipalp of male holotype (MV K- 14856) A ventral view B baso-ventral view C apico-ventral view D apical view. Arrow in A, B points to the tubercle on median apophysis arch. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686602" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">3A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CD0259B0D3DD72AEE7D1BCD31998A468" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19C</figureCitation>
); embolus strong and slightly sinuous (Figs 
<figureCitation id="788D0F8667F8256C806C81A9B5913142" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Salsa rueda sp. nov., expanded left pedipalp of male holotype (MV K- 14856) A ventral view B baso-ventral view C apico-ventral view D apical view. Arrow in A, B points to the tubercle on median apophysis arch. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686602" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">3A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="17FD69DFC561EBE4BC76FAD4108A446A" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="4BB869C43B368DD850D97A6346E392E3" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" start="Figure 20" startId="F20">
<paragraph id="504DB9FB27C693C3C90F5E8FE68480ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="477A02744067C0351AAB0DA8297006E5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Figure 20.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="15EC15B5BACFEBEADD5791AD5F52DEFD" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa rueda" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rueda">
<emphasis id="56BC66F5BB51FDD661EADB95739401D0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa rueda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., female (AM KS.50201) 
<emphasis id="33C7772FBF4BCA2D423C198B5C58A737" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A</emphasis>
dorsal habitus 
<emphasis id="9020221B11A761B2244CF757E672632C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">B</emphasis>
ventral habitus 
<emphasis id="7B0322980926C57DF4E0236B30C1FC33" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C</emphasis>
epigyne, ventral view 
<emphasis id="164513836E8F977217568406179BC2F7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">D</emphasis>
epigyne, lateral view 
<emphasis id="AD059B28868C1E246DA48AD28DA141E7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">E</emphasis>
epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (
<emphasis id="C45ABB982C6E751627B0B9E7593A89B2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A, B</emphasis>
); 0.1 mm (
<emphasis id="A5B41AFBB969E3EAD50333CF02BF209F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C-E</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="AAA0E9F9678A7AF08248EDE00D3DD96F" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="0EFDE2CABEF2A1E8BD18F47C26FA089F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Female</emphasis>
(based on AM KS.50201): Total length 10.5. Carapace 4.2 long, 3.5 wide; reddish brown, slightly paler in cephalic area and posteriorly, covered by white setae specifically in cephalic area (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F3C0F77D231E5BF25202D10CBA25C92F" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.18, ALE 0.16, PME 0.13, PLE 0.11; row of eyes: AME 0.54, PME 0.52, PLE 2.18. Chelicerae reddish brown, four promarginal teeth (apical and second basal largest) and three retromarginal teeth (basal largest). Legs orange-brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="89DEAA87C549A1EF79DA89C2295D4460" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20A, B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + tarsus = total length): 1.1 + 0.4 + 0.7 + 1.3 = 3.5. Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 4.0 + 1.7 + 3.5 + 3.3 + 1.2 = 13.7, II - 3.7 + 1.6 + 2.8 + 2.9 + 1.1 = 12.1, III - 2.5 + 1.1 + 1.4 + 1.5 + 0.8 = 7.3, IV - 3.5 + 1.6 + 2.2 + 2.6 + 1.0 = 10.9. Labium 0.58 long, 0.86 wide, dark brown; endites dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1203B8B518305AD1F4B7E3810EF339EC" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.8 long, 1.6 wide, dark reddish brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7B0FAFFF60C727A1422B8664092058B9" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 6.0 long, 6.0 wide; dorsum beige with indistinct darker folium pattern (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="EEA64AEE269B6F42BF9A65DAF8835212" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20A</figureCitation>
); venter black and laterally with elongate white patches and pale transverse band behind epigastric furrow (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8834EC7B1602D421F6C4554519A5F3DC" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20B</figureCitation>
). Epigyne much longer than wide; atrium with central elevated section and a transverse ridge anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C83764B25D4B846ACFE002870D630055" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20C</figureCitation>
); scape shorter than half the length of epigyne base (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="12AF3A67AD88A372ABE4A800B766EC4C" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20C, D</figureCitation>
); central division a conspicuous narrow ridge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AD0C12D7CEB56164A4C5A7DDD51B26F2" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20E</figureCitation>
). Spermathecae rounded and located on the basis of the genitalia, separated by the width of the median ridge (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3CF974012648347052E4EAB952D110A4" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Salsa gen. nov. female epigynes, cleared posterior view A S. fuliginata (L. Koch, 1872), comb. nov. (CVIC 173) B S. brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov. (AM KS. 131087) C S. canalae comb. nov. Berland, 1924, comb. nov. (WAM T 75921) D S. recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov. (WAM T 77362) E S. rueda sp. nov. F S. tartara sp. nov. (AM KS. 7061). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686604" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">5E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BECE0B09A6770CF57FE34BF1AFE4504E" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="variation">
<paragraph id="479DD4035BB44C78209796353624C94E" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC15FCDE3538BD5DC8DC932C63DC0DF9" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Total length males 6.0-6.8 (
<emphasis id="52BA215FB495C7A98D7A7938AB30CD1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">n</emphasis>
= 5); females 7.2-10.5 (
<emphasis id="0D1C8A68E7B1A550F15A92B094A7631C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">n</emphasis>
= 4). The colour variations in 
<taxonomicName id="9083D1545DF32F15965F2776AA84DB40" genus="S." lsidName="S. rueda" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="rueda">
<emphasis id="D1216EED6F9366D00CC25224661D69B6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. rueda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. are probably the most uniform with the patterns in the folium often little expressed (Figs 
<figureCitation id="C646E4074100369766E761015CEC9C9C" captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Salsa rueda sp. nov., male holotype (MV K- 14856) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686618" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">19A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="8E2E1E266BC514A2400E901BDC4A9435" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figure 20. Salsa rueda sp. nov., female (AM KS. 50201) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.1 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure20" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686619" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">20A</figureCitation>
). There was no evidence of scape breakage in any of the females examined by us.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4632F686C0BE506B80A2402F3EBC3771" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="life history and habitat preferences">
<paragraph id="0DC67679BC5588BC62036C18FBF124B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Life history and habitat preferences.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D0E7AAD2E339BEDE861DCE23A6DA05E" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Specimens were collected in December and January, with a single female from March, indicating this species to be summer-mature. There was no habitat information on any of the specimen labels.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="148042D322A2D8817B07BD38B287EBF9" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="AF03ED3548FC15741D66734AE43954D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="21560B62016D2F9B85354F82E4988D23" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="3FF05D5936A294DE4DD9EDBC626298C6" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa rueda" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rueda">
<emphasis id="CEB631697B8CD7F5BB445692FB24F5C1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa rueda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. were found in the Australian Capital Territory, New South Wales, Victoria, and Tasmania (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E0E547A3E05DFAD91D360865C7AC6C10" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figure 21. Distribution records of Salsa rueda sp. nov. and Salsa tartara sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure21" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686620" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">21</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
